{"body": "Frankly I would disable JSON/XML params parsing by default if I had to pick one of the two to spring in an upgrade.  A lot fewer people use those than use joins.\r\n\r\nThe mysql behavior is only an issue when the bind values are params that came in forced to a type you don't expect, right?\r\n\r\nThis is the only time you'll hear me say this, but: Perl's hacky tainting concept does potentially have some useful ideas here.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/13415917", "created_at": "2013-02-12T02:53:54Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9207#issuecomment-13415917", "updated_at": "2013-02-12T02:53:54Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9207, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/willbryant", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f1c9a2d6b6be7599854a75793ecd872d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60be21f3ebf28ff7b8a692a752d92cf8.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/received_events", "gravatar_id": "f1c9a2d6b6be7599854a75793ecd872d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "willbryant", "type": "User", "id": 12062, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/willbryant/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ec25bd3543c151009c51"}, "id": 13415917, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9207"}
